2500|$|The {{portrayal}} <b>of</b> <b>Mormons</b> in Cold Case {{has also}} drawn criticism from Chris Hicks for being disrespectful. He {{has stated that}} the program {{is an example of}} the unequal treatment <b>of</b> <b>Mormons,</b> stating that where insane people of other religions are portrayed in television drama, pains are taken to point out as part of the plot that they are [...] "non-practicing", yet no such pains are taken when it comes to Mormons. As a result, the faith is seen as directly related to the insanity of one character with the implication being that all Mormons are strange people. He also expressed concerns that the temple garments <b>of</b> <b>Mormons</b> did not receive the same sympathetic dramatic treatment or respect as do the sacred symbols of other religions.|$|R
